    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-12-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 406/22.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-12-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 488.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In further reference to the subject of the
                    arrangement by exchange of notes with such of my colleagues as may be duly
                    authorized by their Governments for that purpose for the reciprocal protection
                    of our trade-marks in China, I have the honor to inform you that the Spanish
                    minister has advised me that he was unable to exchange such assurances with me,
                    as Spanish consuls in China were not empowered to hear cases involving
                    infringement of trade-marks.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
